   <span class="label">(9)</span>
  </div> Note that, although the harvest is resolved as a size spectrum, there is only a single scalar value of effort for a given fish group 
  <span class="italic">k</span> at a given location and time, since it is assumed that the fishing effort does not discriminate among size within each group, other than as determined by the gear type through the selectivity function.
 </p>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">We assume that cost is proportional to effort [
  <a rid="pone.0169763.ref037" ref-type="bibr" href="#pone.0169763.ref037">37</a>], such that 
  <div id="pone.0169763.e011" class="disp-formula">
